question: Which are the predominant rotavirus genotypes around the world?
ideal_answer: The predominant RV genotypes circulating all over the world are G1P[8], G2P[4], G3P[8], G4P[8], and G9P[8], while G12[P6] and G12[P8] are emerging genotypes.
